      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 2:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and stones, or pieces of stones, might lie about, with which they furnished themselves, in order to have destroyed Christ: and this they attempted, though it was on the sabbath day, as appears from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 9:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and with them, , \"stoning on the sabbath day\" (d) was allowed in some cases. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But Jesus hid himself, not in any corner of the temple, or behind a pillar; but he withdrew himself from them directly, and made himself invisible to them, by holding their eyes, or casting a mist before them, that they could not see him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and went out of the temple; by one of the gates of it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "going through the midst of them; not of the persons that took up stones to stone him; but the rest of the people, who were there in great multitudes to hear his doctrine, and see his miracles: and so passed by, and escaped out of their hands; the last words, going through the midst of them, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and so passed by, are not in Beza's most ancient copy, and in the Vulgate Latin version. ",
        "children": []
